https://packaging.python.org/en/latest/guides/installing-using-pip-and-virtual-environments/
python -m venv .venv
Create a new virtual env called .venv (Hidden)

source .venv/bin/activate
Activate the virtual env

pip list
Show all the packages installed

pip freeze > requirements.txt
Set the installed packages into a txt file called requirements

pip install -r requirements.txt
Install all the packages in the requirements file

deactivate
Deactivate the virtual env

which python
Show where Python is ran from

python -m pip install --upgrade pip
Upgrade pip

python -m pip install yfinance
python -m pip install --upgrade yfinance
Install/Upgrade the package in the virtual env

